{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:24:04.436Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sigmoid"},{"type":"text","text":" is one of the earliest and most foundational activation functions in neural networks. It maps any input value to a range between 0 and 1 using an S-shaped curve, making it ideal for interpreting outputs as probabilities."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What is Sigmoid?"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mathematical definition:"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\sigma(x) = \\frac{1}{1 + e^{-x}}"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Zo47Ry8RRw)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where:\n- "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"x"}},{"type":"text","text":" = input value (weighted sum + bias from a neuron)\n- "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"e"}},{"type":"text","text":" = Euler's number ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"e \\approx 2.718"}},{"type":"text","text":"), base of natural logarithm"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual representation (S-shaped curve):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sigmoid(x):\n  1 │        ╱───\n    │      ╱\n    │    ╱\n0.5 │──╱───────  ←passes through (0, 0.5)\n    │ ╱\n    │╱\n  0 ┼───────────> x\n    │"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For positive "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"x"}},{"type":"text","text":": output asymptotically approaches 1\nFor negative "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"x"}},{"type":"text","text":": output asymptotically approaches 0\nAt "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"x = 0"}},{"type":"text","text":": output = 0.5"}]},{"type":"paragraph","conte